Greetings to all, I may not be a food critique, but even a six-year-old would throw a fit with how horrible the customer service is at this location. I went to this location with two friends, and one of them was immediately confronted by an employee, asking if he wants a cookie. My friend was puzzled and continued to further ask if the cookie was free, thinking the employee was asking out of generosity. However, the employee frustratingly responded by saying, "No, it's because you're standing in the line". My friend, who is a very easy going person, shrugged off this employee's rudeness with humor. I proceeded to go near him to order, and then he rudely pointed me away to the other side of the line. I was quite frankly through at this point but considering proximity, this was the only available Subway. Overall, I would highly, highly recommend that if anyone is looking to eat Subway, make the extra trip and go to any other location but this one.
